00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:57,550
Yes, it's no big deal.

266
00:14:57,550 --> 00:14:59,650
Why were you in a place like that?

267
00:14:59,650 --> 00:15:01,250
That person...

268
00:15:01,250 --> 00:15:04,450
I saw somebody that resembled Yayoi's older brother, so I...

269
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:06,750
What? My older brother?

270
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:08,150
I went after him,

271
00:15:08,150 --> 00:15:11,250
and suddenly the stone from a stone fence came falling...

272
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:14,250
Putting salt in canned coffee is not that serious,

273
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,650
but this is going a bit too far.

274
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:18,750
It's the same, isn't it?

275
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:20,950
-With the seven wonders. -Huh?

276
00:15:20,950 --> 00:15:23,150
Audio man Mr. Yatsukawa's coffee

277
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:25,550
was spoiled with salt poured into it.

278
00:15:26,650 --> 00:15:28,850
The sound of wooden clappers that was set as the ringtone

279
00:15:28,850 --> 00:15:32,250
before he noticed anything had been changed.

280
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:34,650
The thing that hurt Ms. Miyake, in charge of make-up

281
00:15:34,650 --> 00:15:36,950
was a blotched stone.

282
00:15:36,950 --> 00:15:39,950
They are each objects of the 7 Wonders of Misen.

283
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:41,550
The Ebb and Flow Rock,

284
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:43,450
the sound of the wooden clappers,

285
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:46,050
and the Mandala Rock. Don't they all match?

286
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:47,250
True!

287
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:50,750
It's amazing that you noticed, sonny!

288
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:52,850
Stay out of it, kid.

289
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:54,750
That's only three out of seven!

290
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:56,850
It's just a coincidence, understand? A coincidence!

291
00:15:56,850 --> 00:15:59,950
I wonder about that. There could be more.

292
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:01,350
They are!

293
00:16:01,350 --> 00:16:05,450
Assistant Producer, Mr. Kitayama's necktie,

294
00:16:05,450 --> 00:16:07,950
the pattern on it is the Dewy Cherry Blossoms, right?

295
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:09,450
Now that you mentioned it.

296
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:13,750
Yeah, it was of bad taste that was out of season.

297
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,950
One more of the 7 Wonders,

298
00:16:15,950 --> 00:16:17,650
Dewy Cherry Blossoms!

299
00:16:19,350 --> 00:16:21,350
Then, maybe...

300
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:22,850
And his stomachache...

301
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:25,150
It could've been caused by somebody too?

302
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,950
By somebody...

303
00:16:26,950 --> 00:16:29,550
Do you mean Yayoi's older brother?

304
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:31,450
Oh, no.

305
00:16:31,450 --> 00:16:34,250
If so, but why us?

306
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:36,850
You have no idea as to why?

307
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:41,150
Maybe you should also go ask Mr. Kitamura?

308
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:42,850
I know.

309
00:16:42,850 --> 00:16:44,750
Mr. Kamisuwa.

310
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:53,650
He's not answering.

311
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:55,650
I wonder if he's sleeping?

312
00:16:55,650 --> 00:16:58,650
Just to be safe, let's have the hotel staff go check on him.

313
00:17:03,950 --> 00:17:07,250
I see. So he's asleep after all.

314
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:10,550
Then, please leave him a message to call us when he gets up.

315
00:17:10,550 --> 00:17:13,350
Thank you so very much.

316
00:17:13,350 --> 00:17:15,850
There are three 7 wonders left.

317
00:17:15,850 --> 00:17:18,750
Is something else going to happen yet?

318
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:21,250
And, besides that guy...

319
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:24,250
Is Yayoi's older brother really involved?

320
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:26,650
Wait a sec.

321
00:17:26,650 --> 00:17:30,350
Her older brother disappeared two weeks ago and...

322
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:34,250
That photo was also placed there two weeks ago.

323
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,250
Maybe...

324
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:39,350
Her older brother saw the picture and...

325
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:41,550
What shall we do, Mr. Kamisuwa?

326
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:44,050
What's scheduled today?

327
00:17:44,050 --> 00:17:47,550
After this, we go over to Daishoin and that's it!

328
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:49,950
Then, filming is priority.

329
00:17:49,950 --> 00:17:52,750
We'll talk about this again tonight or something.

330
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:54,350
I'm sorry, Mr. Mouri,

331
00:17:54,350 --> 00:17:56,050
but I hope that's okay with you.

332
00:17:56,050 --> 00:17:57,950
Okay.

333
00:17:57,950 --> 00:17:59,450
Okay, let's move it then!

334
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:00,650
Yes, sir!

335
00:18:00,650 --> 00:18:03,550
"Daishoin"

336
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:17,150
Cut!

337
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:19,450
Okay, all done!

338
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:22,550
Thanks for all the work, everyone!

339
00:18:22,550 --> 00:18:24,950
We've only got one more scene to go today!

340
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,650
There's something about those two.

341
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:31,950
I'd better keep my eyes on them.

342
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:34,450
"Kannon Hall"

343
00:18:34,450 --> 00:18:36,950
Next, is the mental training in the dark

344
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:38,450
that helps get rid of the sins of this world,

345
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:40,350
climbing the "Ordination Platform"!

346
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:43,250
Ran, Conan, we're counting on you!

347
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:46,250
Huh, you mean we're going in here all by ourselves?

348
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:49,550
I'm not too comfortable with things like this.

349
00:18:49,550 --> 00:18:50,750
Rather, this is bad,

350
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:53,450
because I'm not going to be able to watch those two.

351
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:56,050
Hey, you're a boy, don't be a panty!

352
00:18:56,050 --> 00:18:57,550
Go on, go on!

353
00:18:57,550 --> 00:18:59,450
Give it all you got, Ran!

354
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:01,850
Come on, inside, inside!

355
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:06,950
Hey, Conan.

356
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:08,550
Don't go without me.

357
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:10,450
Let's go together, Conan.

358
00:19:13,650 --> 00:19:15,450
We're finally outside.

359
00:19:15,450 --> 00:19:18,450
That's all for today.

360
00:19:18,450 --> 00:19:21,650
We'll see you again tomorrow!

361
00:19:21,650 --> 00:19:23,450
Thank you so very much.

362
00:19:26,250 --> 00:19:29,750
Huh? Where are Mr. Kamisuwa and Mr. Koshiji?

363
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,550
Somebody, come here!

364
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:33,250
What was that?

365
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:42,050
Mr. Kamisuwa?

366
00:19:45,550 --> 00:19:47,450
Mr. Koshiji!

367
00:19:47,450 --> 00:19:49,650
This is...

368
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:53,350
Mr. Koshiji!

369
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:54,850
He's still breathing.

370
00:19:54,850 --> 00:19:57,750
Mr. Yatsukawa, call an ambulance!

371
00:19:57,750 --> 00:20:00,850
Fire... He was there...

372
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:03,350
What?

373
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:05,350
Fire? He was there?

374
00:20:05,350 --> 00:20:07,150
Who was there?

375
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:09,050
-The culprit? -What?

376
00:20:09,050 --> 00:20:11,050
Mr. Koshiji, once more!

377
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:14,050
No good, he passed out.

378
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:19,350
This is...

379
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:21,150
The strap of his cell phone is...

380
00:20:21,150 --> 00:20:22,750
the tin staff!

381
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:26,850
A small replica of the Tin Staff Plum, one of the 7 wonders?

382
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:28,650
Did the culprit drop it?

383
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:31,350
It's him.

384
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,450
Huh?

385
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:36,850
I saw the guy we saw in the afternoon run off beyond.

386
00:20:36,850 --> 00:20:39,050
Why didn't you say so sooner?

387
00:20:39,050 --> 00:20:41,350
Don't tell me he's planning to flee on the ferry.

388
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:00,750
Will I make it?

389
00:21:02,850 --> 00:21:04,850
-Excuse me! -I'm sorry!

390
00:21:12,950 --> 00:21:14,150
Where's the ferry?

391
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:21,850
Too late?

392
00:21:21,850 --> 00:21:23,850
Hey, that!

393
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:30,850
It's that guy!

394
00:21:30,850 --> 00:21:33,050
Darn it! We almost got him!

395
00:21:33,050 --> 00:21:36,950
Big trouble! Misenya's on fire!

396
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:38,750
What?

397
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:41,250
Fire, the shop, eh?

398
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:47,950
Somebody! Somebody!

399
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:54,550
-Did you bring water? -Hurry up!

400
00:21:54,550 --> 00:21:56,950
-Yayoi! -Are you all right?

401
00:21:56,950 --> 00:21:58,650
Yes.

402
00:22:04,050 --> 00:22:05,750
Kitamura?

403
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:08,850
Mr. Kamisuwa, I'm sorry for the inconvenience I caused.

404
00:22:08,850 --> 00:22:10,850
This is no time for something like that right now.

405
00:22:10,850 --> 00:22:13,450
Koshiji's been attacked and Misenya's on fire.

406
00:22:13,450 --> 00:22:15,450
Huh? Mr. Koshiji's been attacked?

407
00:22:15,450 --> 00:22:17,250
A fire? What's going on?

408
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:20,550
Mr. Kitamura who's resting at a hotel in Hiroshima...

409
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:24,450
Mr. Kamisuwa! This is bad!

